title: Bombers players' cars nicked in burglary
text:
Home invaders steal Essendon players' cars By AAP Essendon Bombers players. (AAP file image) 
Essendon players have reportedly had their cars stolen by baseball bat wielding intruders during a home invasion in Melbourne. 
Police say four offenders armed with baseball bats broke into the Maribyrnong house early on Friday morning and stole wallets and keys before driving off in four cars. 
One of the residents woke up after hearing one of the vehicles, a Volkswagen, crash nearby and saw a man jump out and get into another vehicle. 
It's believed the offenders arrived at the property in a stolen Toyota Camry, which was later found dumped in Maribyrnong. 
The Volkswagen stolen from the property has also been recovered nearby. 
The other three vehicles, a Mazda and two Holden Commodores have not been found. 
The cars belong to Essendon players, 3AW is reporting. 
The Essendon Football Club has been contacted for comment. Â© AAP 2017
